2 unit(s) Chicken Breasts
4 tbsp Soy Sauce Mirin Blend
4 tbsp Teriyaki Sauce
1 tbsp Garlic Puree
4 tbsp All-Purpose Flour
¾ cup Jasmine Rice
2 unit(s) Green Onion
227 g Broccoli
0.44 tsp Salt*
2 tbsp Oil*
0.38 tsp Pepper*

Add 1 cup (2 cups) water and 1/8 tsp (1/4 tsp) salt to a medium pot. Cover and bring to a boil over high heat.
Meanwhile, using a strainer, rinse rice until water runs clear.
Add rice to the boiling water, then reduce heat to medium-low. Cover and cook until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, 12-14 min. (NOTE: Reduce heat to low if water is boiling over.)
Remove from heat. Set aside, still covered.

Meanwhile, thinly slice green onions.
Cut broccoli into bite-sized pieces.
Add soy sauce mirin blend, teriyaki sauce, garlic puree and 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) water to a small bowl. Season with pepper, then stir to combine.

Combine flour, 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) salt and 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) pepper in a medium bowl.
Pat chicken dry with paper towels. Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Add chicken to flour mixture and toss to coat.
Using your hands, press flour mixture into chicken to coat completely.

Add broccoli and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil to an unlined baking sheet. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.
Roast in the middle of the oven until golden-brown, 12-14 min.
Meanwhile, heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then chicken. Cook, flipping occasionally, until golden-brown and cooked through, 8-10 min.**

When chicken is almost cooked through, add teriyaki mixture. Stir to combine. Cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly reduced, 1-2 min.

Fluff rice with a fork.
Divide rice between plates. Top with broccoli and teriyaki chicken.
Sprinkle green onions over top.

If you've opted to get chicken breasts, pat dry with paper towels, then cut into 1-inch pieces. Cook them in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the diced chicken.